{
  "name": "Degenerative Myelopathy (DM)",
  "slug": "degenerative-myelopathy",
  "category": "Neurological",
  "description": "DM is a progressive, non-painful spinal cord disease caused by a mutation in the SOD1 gene. It begins with hind limb weakness and ataxia, progressing to complete paralysis and eventually fore limb involvement. It is analogous to ALS in humans.",
  "symptoms": [
    "Progressive hind limb weakness",
    "Knuckling of hind paws",
    "Dragging hind legs",
    "Loss of bladder and bowel control",
    "Loss of muscle mass"
  ],
  "severity": "high",
  "treatment_overview": "There is no cure or disease-modifying treatment. Intensive physiotherapy and hydrotherapy can slow decline and maintain quality of life. Wheelchairs improve mobility in later stages.",
